Patch summary:
Set release aconfig defaults needed by the desktop build. Quick Settings stays
on the known-good non-Compose path because the desktop QS customizations target
the classic implementation, including the tile removals and panel interaction
behavior used by this VM.

This also enables Launcher3 desktop visual-effect and mouse-interaction flags
in the generated release flag sets. Keeping those values here makes the
behavior reproducible across both trunk staging and BP4A-style builds instead
of depending on runtime flag edits after first boot.

LineageOS 23.2 selects the stable BP4A target. Carry the core desktop windowing
values plus the user-facing trunk polish into that release config as read-only
values. This restores cutout-aware taskbar layout, taskbar customization,
desktop transition motion, modern borders and shadows, connected-display
behavior, desktop mouse interaction, the Bubble Anything launcher/bubble-bar
path and its trunk stability fixes, and related correctness fixes without
enabling diagnostic logging, Launcher model rewrites, or the experimental
WindowDecoration2 refactor.

